about_content><div id=ge_summary_v><div class="hproduct"><table id="summary_content_table" cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0><tr><td id="bookinfo"><h1 class="booktitle"><span class="fn"><span dir=ltr>Oil Wealth and the Fate of the Forest</span></span>: <span class="subtitle"><span dir=ltr>A Comparative Study of Eight Tropical Countries</span></span></h1><div class="bookcover"><img src="https://books.google.com/books/content?id=n2nQ0A8BmCYC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&imgtk=AFLRE72uIcTmVSMvVEXKpXmiuvNc-S88VGCTJf1W1iOw0Ek3fktdJHRexYtfUuEM2ArnnBX3-M9qojLYmkdsZX1l7YCXaGo735of_wsfK6JzvR9tlPLCvDH3iYrCMIWWNoTnj2k8wO5C" alt="Front Cover" title="Front Cover" width=128 border=1 id=summary-frontcover ></div><div class="bookinfo_sectionwrap"><div><a href="https://www.google.com/search?tbo=p&amp;tbm=bks&amp;q=inauthor:%22Sven+Wunder%22" class="secondary"><span dir=ltr>Sven Wunder</span></a></div><div><span dir=ltr>Taylor &amp; Francis</span>, <span dir=ltr>Apr 24, 2003</span> - <a class="secondary" href="https://www.google.com/search?tbo=p&amp;tbm=bks&amp;q=subject:%22Business+%26+Economics%22&amp;source=gbs_ge_summary_r&amp;cad=0"><span dir=ltr>Business &amp; Economics</span></a> - <span dir=ltr>456 pages</span></div></div><div id=synopsis><div id=synopsis-window><div id=synopsistext dir=ltr class="sa"><p>Reduction in the size of the world's remaining rainforests is an issue of huge importance for all societies. This new book - an analysis of the impact of oil wealth on tropical deforestation in South America, Africa and Asia - takes a much more analytical approach than the usual fare of environmental studies. </p> <p>The focus on economies as a whole leads to a more balanced view than those that are often put forward and therefore, vitally, a view that is more valid. Of use to those who study environmental issues and economics, this book is potentially an indispensable tool for policy-makers the world over.</p></div></div></div><div class="search_box_wrapper"></div></td> </tr><